{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":34504,"record_hash":"sha256:324bc46421b5ed40069e89f86dbbdcd72f1f13fcd5d3f82b6a0b3e8023cea311","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:52:19.360Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n\\n- **P1** [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:137](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:137): `sync_metadata()` always pulls before the first push, so first sync to an empty but correctly configured metadata remote fails with `fatal: couldn't find remote ref refs/meta/main`. I reproduced: `capture` succeeded, then `agentlog sync` failed at `failed to pull GitMeta metadata`. The test hides this by pre-initializing the remote with `session.push_once(Some(\\\"origin\\\"))` before calling `Command::Sync` at [crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:356](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:356). Small fix: cover a truly empty metadata remote and either skip/handle the missing-remote-ref pull or let the first push path initialize it.\\n\\n- **P3** [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:134](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:134): `sync_metadata()` resolves the GitMeta remote, then passes `Some(&remote)` into `pull`, `push_once`, and `resolve_push_conflict`, all of which already validate/resolve the configured metadata remote. This duplicates GitMeta transport selection in the agentlog boundary. Small cleanup: drop the explicit `resolve_remote(None)` and pass `None` through to GitMeta unless agentlog needs to report or choose a remote itself.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:52:19.360Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}